---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Pratyangira Homam | Protection Ritual | Nagayakshi Temple">

  <section class="pooja-hero">
    <div class="pooja-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="pooja-hero-content">
      <span class="pooja-badge">Quarterly Homam</span>
      <h1>Pratyangira Homam</h1>
      <p class="pooja-tagline">Sacred fire ritual invoking the fierce Goddess to destroy negative forces and protect devotees</p>
      <div class="pooja-quick-info">
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Frequency</span>
          <span class="info-value">Quarterly</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Duration</span>
          <span class="info-value">4&#8211;5 hours</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Starting From</span>
          <span class="info-value">&#8377;10,000</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="#booking" class="btn-primary-gold">Book This Homam</a>
        <a href="#details" class="btn-secondary-outline">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Is This Ritual -->
  <section class="pooja-section" id="details">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What is Pratyangira Homam?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <p class="intro-text">
            Pratyangira Homam is an extraordinarily powerful fire ritual performed to invoke
            Goddess Pratyangira&#8212;the fierce, lion-faced form of Shakti who destroys all
            forms of negative energy, black magic, evil eye, and enemy afflictions. This homam
            is among the most potent protective rituals in the Tantric tradition, capable of
            reversing curses and neutralizing even the most deeply rooted negative influences.
          </p>
          <h3>Three Dimensions of Protection</h3>
          <p>The homam addresses three distinct sources of negative influence:</p>
          <div class="variant-cards">
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>1. Abhichara Nivarana</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Black magic &amp; tantric attacks<br>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> To neutralize spells, hexes, and dark tantric workings
                directed against the devotee or their family
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>2. Drishti Dosha Removal</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Evil eye &amp; negative gaze<br>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> To cleanse the aura of harmful energies cast through
                jealousy, envy, or ill-will from others
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>3. Shatru Nashana</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Enemy afflictions &amp; legal matters<br>
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> To protect against enemies, false accusations, court cases,
                and those who seek to cause harm
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4>Quick Facts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>One of the most powerful protective rituals</li>
              <li>Performed quarterly at auspicious times</li>
              <li>Requires strict purity observances</li>
              <li>Conducted by Ambotti Thampuran</li>
              <li>Limited participants per session</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box highlight">
            <h4>Best For</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Black magic &amp; evil eye victims</li>
              <li>Court case &amp; legal trouble</li>
              <li>Enemies causing harm</li>
              <li>Unexplained chronic misfortune</li>
              <li>Business failure &amp; loss</li>
              <li>Family under dark influence</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Traditional Basis -->
  <section class="tradition-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Sacred Origins</span>
        <h2>The Tradition of Pratyangira</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-story">
        <div class="story-image">
          <img src="/images/pratyangira.png" alt="Goddess Pratyangira">
        </div>
        <div class="story-content">
          <h3>The Fierce Protector Goddess</h3>
          <p>
            Goddess Pratyangira is described in the Atharvana Veda and Tantric scriptures as
            a form of supreme Shakti with a lion&#8217;s head and human body, blazing with
            thousand-armed radiance. She is said to have emerged when Lord Shiva took the
            form of Sharabha to subdue Narasimha, and Pratyangira arose from this cosmic
            encounter as the most powerful anti-dark force in creation.
          </p>
          <p>
            At Sree Pulikkal Vishwanagayakshi Temple, the Pratyangira Homam is performed
            in the tradition of <strong>Kerala Tantra Shastra</strong>, combining the power
            of the Naga deities with the fierce energy of Pratyangira for maximum protective
            efficacy. The combination makes this one of the most effective remedies available
            in this region.
          </p>
          <div class="scripture-quote">
            <p>
              &#8220;She who is Pratyangira destroys all abhichara&#8212;all black arts directed
              against the devotee. There is no dark force that can withstand her lion&#8217;s roar.&#8221;
            </p>
            <span class="quote-attribution">&#8212; Atharvana Veda, Tantric Commentary</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tradition-variants">
        <h3>The Homam Process</h3>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Sankalpa &amp; Purification</h4>
          <p>
            The homam begins with a detailed sankalpa (sacred intention-setting) where the
            priest takes the devotee&#8217;s full name, nakshatra, gotra, and the specific
            affliction to be addressed. The ritual space is purified using sacred ash, turmeric
            water, and Naga mantras to create a protected ceremonial field.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>The Sacred Fire Ritual</h4>
          <p>
            The fire pit (kunda) is consecrated with 108 names of Pratyangira while specific
            oblations&#8212;including sesame, black mustard, turmeric, and sacred herbs&#8212;are
            offered into the fire with each mantra. The priest performs 1,008 to 10,008 ahutis
            (fire offerings) depending on the severity of the affliction, calling upon Pratyangira
            to absorb and destroy all negative forces.
          </p>
          <p>
            The ritual concludes with a protective kavacham (armor) being recited over the
            devotee, and sacred ash from the homam is given as prasadam for continued protection.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Should Perform -->
  <section class="pooja-section audience-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Who Should Perform Pratyangira Homam?</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">This powerful ritual is especially beneficial for those facing these specific situations</p>
      </div>
      <div class="audience-grid">
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Black Magic Victims</h3>
          <p>Those experiencing sudden, unexplained misfortune that began after conflicts with specific people or visits to certain places.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="6"/><path d="M15.477 12.89L17 22l-5-3-5 3 1.523-9.11"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Evil Eye Afflicted</h3>
          <p>Individuals or families who feel they are subject to Drishti (evil eye) from envious people, causing health or prosperity issues.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M3 6h18M3 12h18M3 18h18"/><path d="M9 3v18M15 3v18"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Legal &amp; Court Troubles</h3>
          <p>Those entangled in prolonged legal cases, false accusations, or disputes that seem to inexplicably drag on despite rightful cause.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Business Failure</h3>
          <p>Entrepreneurs experiencing repeated business collapses, broken partnerships, or financial disasters despite sincere efforts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Family Under Dark Influence</h3>
          <p>Families where multiple members face simultaneous misfortunes&#8212;accidents, illness, relationship breakdowns&#8212;suggesting a household-level negative influence.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <div class="audience-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Psychic Disturbances</h3>
          <p>Individuals experiencing recurring nightmares, unexplained fears, disturbed sleep, or a sense of being followed or watched by negative presences.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="pricing-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Homam Pricing</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-grid single-price">
        <div class="price-card featured">
          <div class="price-badge">Complete Ritual</div>
          <div class="price-header">
            <h3>Pratyangira Homam</h3>
            <div class="price-amount">
              <span class="currency">&#8377;</span>
              <span class="amount">10,000</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="price-features">
            <h4>Includes:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Full 4&#8211;5 hour fire ritual</li>
              <li>1,008 ahutis (fire offerings)</li>
              <li>Personal sankalpa with name &amp; nakshatra</li>
              <li>Abhishekam of Pratyangira Yantra</li>
              <li>Protective kavacham recitation</li>
              <li>Sacred ash prasadam (vibhuti)</li>
              <li>Post-homam Naga blessings</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <a href="#booking" class="price-cta">Book Now</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-note">
        <p><strong>Note:</strong> Due to the intensity of this ritual, participation is limited. Please contact us in advance to confirm availability. Prasadam shipping charges apply for locations outside Kerala.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I know if I need Pratyangira Homam?</summary>
          <p>
            If you are experiencing sudden, unexplained misfortune; recurring nightmares or
            disturbed sleep; failing health despite medical treatment; business collapses;
            or if troubles started after a conflict with a specific person&#8212;these can
            be signs of negative influence. Contact Ambotti Thampuran for a consultation.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I perform this homam as a preventive measure?</summary>
          <p>
            Yes. Many devotees perform Pratyangira Homam once a year as a spiritual
            &#8220;cleanse&#8221; to remove accumulated negative energies and strengthen
            their protective aura, even without specific afflictions. The quarterly schedule
            makes this accessible as a regular protective practice.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do I need to be present in person?</summary>
          <p>
            While physical presence is always preferred and more effective, the homam can
            be performed on your behalf with your name, nakshatra, and gotra. Sacred ash
            (vibhuti) and other prasadam will be dispatched to your address after the ritual.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How many sessions are needed?</summary>
          <p>
            For mild Drishti or evil eye issues, a single session is often sufficient.
            For long-standing black magic or severe afflictions, 3 consecutive quarterly
            sessions (one year of homams) are recommended for complete resolution.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What preparations should I make before attending?</summary>
          <p>
            Observe all temple protocols: no alcohol, no non-vegetarian food on the day,
            maintain purity guidelines. Wear traditional attire if attending in person.
            Bring details of your nakshatra and gotra. Arrive with a clear intention of
            what you wish to be protected from or resolved.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Booking CTA -->
  <section class="booking-cta-section" id="booking">
    <div class="booking-cta-container">
      <h2>Book Pratyangira Homam</h2>
      <p>
        Next scheduled: <strong>Contact us for the upcoming date</strong><br>
        Limited participants per session &#8212; early registration required
      </p>
      <div class="booking-cta-buttons">
        <a href="/register" class="btn-primary-gold btn-large">Book Online Now</a>
        <a href="tel:+919946373522" class="btn-secondary-outline">Call: +91 9946373522</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
/* Hero */
.pooja-hero {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 70vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background:
    linear-gradient(rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.75), rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.9)),
    url('/images/pratyangira.png') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.pooja-hero-overlay {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(212, 165, 116, 0.12) 0%, transparent 60%);
}

.pooja-hero-content {
  max-width: 900px;
  position: relative;
  z-index: 10;
}

.pooja-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  background: var(--laterite-red);
  color: white;
  padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 30px;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 2px;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.pooja-hero h1 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 4.2rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: white;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
}

.pooja-tagline {
  font-size: 1.35rem;
  color: var(--bg-alt);
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.pooja-quick-info {
  display: flex;
  gap: 2rem;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
  padding: 1.8rem 2rem;
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
}

.quick-info-item {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.4rem;
}

.info-label {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: #ffd285;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 1px;
}

.info-value {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  color: white;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.hero-ctas {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

/* Sections */
.pooja-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
}

.pooja-section.audience-section {
  background: var(--bg-alt);
}

.pooja-container {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

/* Content grid */
.content-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
  gap: 3rem;
}

.content-main {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.9;
}

.intro-text {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  color: var(--laterite-dark);
  line-height: 1.9;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.content-main h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.9rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin: 2.5rem 0 1.2rem;
}

.content-main p {
  margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
}

.variant-cards {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.2rem;
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
}

.variant-card {
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  padding: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
}

.variant-card h4 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
}

.variant-card p {
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 0;
}

/* Sidebar */
.content-sidebar {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2rem;
}

.info-box {
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  padding: 1.8rem;
  border-radius: 10px;
  border: 2px solid #e8c9a0;
}

.info-box.highlight {
  background: var(--laterite-dark);
  border-color: var(--gold);
}

.info-box h4 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.info-box.highlight h4 {
  color: #ffd285;
}

.info-box ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
}

.info-box li {
  padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
  position: relative;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
}

.info-box.highlight li {
  color: var(--bg-alt);
  border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
}

.info-box li::before {
  content: '✓';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  font-weight: 700;
}

.info-box.highlight li::before {
  color: var(--gold);
}

/* Tradition section */
.tradition-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
}

.section-label {
  display: block;
  font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--saffron);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 3px;
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.tradition-story {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 420px 1fr;
  gap: 3rem;
  align-items: start;
  margin: 3rem 0;
}

.story-image img {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 12px;
  box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
  filter: sepia(0.15) brightness(0.95);
}

.story-content h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.9rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
}

.story-content p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.9;
  margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
}

.scripture-quote {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 1.8rem;
  border-radius: 10px;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--laterite-red);
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
}

.scripture-quote p {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--laterite-dark);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
}

.quote-attribution {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

.tradition-variants {
  margin-top: 4rem;
}

.tradition-variants h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 2rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.variant-detail {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 2.5rem;
  border-radius: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
}

.variant-detail h4 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.variant-detail p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.8;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.variant-detail strong {
  color: var(--laterite-dark);
}

/* Audience */
.audience-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.8rem;
}

.audience-card {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 2rem;
  border-radius: 12px;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  text-align: center;
}

.audience-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-5px);
  box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
}

.audience-icon {
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  margin: 0 auto 1rem;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
}

.audience-icon svg {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

.audience-card h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.35rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
}

.audience-card p {
  font-size: 0.98rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.section-intro {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}

/* Pricing */
.pricing-section {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
}

.pricing-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(310px, 1fr));
  gap: 2.5rem;
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 3rem auto;
}

.pricing-grid.single-price {
  max-width: 500px;
}

.price-card {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  border-radius: 14px;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 35px rgba(0,0,0,0.09);
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  position: relative;
}

